2. Iterate through s from the beginning to the end.
3. If the last character of t matches the current character of s, increment result and decrement tLength.
4. After iterating through all characters of s, return the result.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the strings s and t. The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a constant amount of space for result and tLength variables. The energy implications are low since the algorithm does not require any additional resources beyond the input strings.

